      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "Card specifies MACS3, but paper describes original MACS (2008). MACS3 is a later version not covered in this paper.",
        "Card lists multiple subcommands (filterdup, predictd, pileup, bdgcmp, bdgopt, bdgpeakcall) that are not documented in the paper. The paper describes MACS as a single integrated tool with command-line parameters, not as a suite of separate subcommands.",
        "Card expects narrowPeak, BEDGRAPH pileup, and BEDGRAPH q-value outputs; paper documents BED and XLS outputs only.",
        "Card focuses on MACS3 subcommand workflow; paper describes MACS as a monolithic algorithm with integrated parameters."
