      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes MACS (2008), not MACS3. No mention of subcommands like 'filterdup', 'predictd', 'pileup', 'bdgcmp', 'bdgopt', or 'bdgpeakcall'. Paper describes MACS as a monolithic algorithm with parameters (--pvalue, --mfold, --bw, etc.), not a modular pipeline of separate subcommands. The card appears to describe a later version (MACS3) with a different architecture than the original MACS paper.",
