    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The candidate card describes MACS3 with a modular subcommand architecture (filterdup, predictd, pileup, bdgcmp, bdgopt, bdgpeakcall), but the paper describes MACS (2008) as a monolithic tool with a single command-line interface and parameter-based options.",
        "The card expects BEDGRAPH format outputs (.bdg files), but the paper explicitly states MACS outputs BED and XLS files only.",
        "The card frames the task as 'reconstructing a manual pipeline' from separate subcommands, but the paper presents MACS as an integrated algorithm where all steps (tag shifting, duplicate removal, lambda modeling, peak calling) are performed by a single tool.",
        "The card references CTCF data with '200K' tags, but the paper describes CTCF ChIP-Seq with 2.9 million tags, not 200K.",
        "The card's research question assumes knowledge of MACS3 subcommand architecture that does not exist in the 2008 MACS paper."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 5,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
