      "asbval:evidence_quote": "MACS removes duplicate tags in excess of what is warranted by the sequencing depth (binomial distribution p-value <10-5). For example, for the 3.9 million FoxA1 ChIP-Seq tags, MACS allows each genomic position to contain no more than one tag and removes all the redundancies.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes duplicate removal as part of MACS peak detection (passage 4), but does not name it 'filterdup' or describe it as a separate preprocessing subcommand. The functionality (removing duplicate tags) is present but the tool name and framing as a separate command-line utility is not explicitly stated in the 2008 MACS paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "bedgraph-file-format-manipulation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "macs3 filterdup",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T17:59:15.228419+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/bedpe-format-handling/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "Paper (2008) describes MACS v1, which processes single-end ChIP-Seq tags from Solexa/Illumina sequencers. No mention of BEDPE format, paired-end reads, or paired-end-aware processing. The paper explicitly states MACS takes BED or ELAND format input and models tag shift size 'd' from single-end tag distributions. BEDPE and paired-end handling are features of MACS3 (a later version not described in this paper).",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "bedpe-format-handling",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Handle paired-end ChIP-Seq data in BEDPE format to preserve fragment pairing information through peak-calling workflows. BEDPE format encodes both read pairs as six-column tab-separated coordinates, enabling proper fragment length estimation and paired-end-aware pileup.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T17:59:27.273705+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/bedpe-format-handling/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes MACS (v1, 2008), not MACS3. The paper does not mention a 'predictd' subcommand. MACS v1 models fragment shift size 'd' as part of the main peak-calling algorithm, not as a separate predictd command. MACS3 is a later version not covered in this paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "bedpe-format-handling",
