      "asbval:evidence_quote": "MACS is implemented in Python and freely available with an open source Artistic License at [16]. It runs from the command line and takes the following parameters: -t for treatment file (ChIP tags, this is the ONLY required parameter for MACS) and -c for control file containing mapped tags",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes MACS (2008) command-line tool, not 'macs3 callpeak'. The paper's MACS tool performs integrated peak calling including duplicate removal, but the command structure and tool name differ from MACS3.",
