      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Therefore, MACS removes duplicate tags in excess of what is warranted by the sequencing depth (binomial distribution p-value <10-5)... For example, for the 3.9 million FoxA1 ChIP-Seq tags, MACS allows each genomic position to contain no more than one tag and removes all the redundancies.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes duplicate removal as part of MACS peak detection workflow, but does not mention a separate 'filterdup' subcommand. Duplicate filtering is integrated into the main MACS algorithm, not a standalone tool.",
