    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/fragment-length-estimation-from-read-pairs/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We present Model-based Analysis of ChIP-Seq data, MACS, which analyzes data generated by short read sequencers such as Solexa's Genome Analyzer.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes MACS (2008), not MACS3. MACS3 is a later version not discussed in this paper. The paper's MACS tool does not provide paired-end analysis subcommands.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "fragment-length-estimation-from-read-pairs",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "MACS3",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:01:05.494169+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/fragment-length-estimation-from-read-pairs/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "ChIP-Seq tags represent the ends of fragments in a ChIP-DNA library and are often shifted towards the 3' direction to better represent the precise protein-DNA interaction site.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper works with single-end tags (5' ends), not paired-end reads. MACS does not accept BEDPE format or paired-end data. The paper's fragment length estimation (shift size 'd') is derived from tag density bimodality on single-end data, not from paired-end coordinates.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "fragment-length-estimation-from-read-pairs",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply this skill when you have paired-end ChIP-Seq data (BEDPE format) and need to determine the empirical fragment length (insertion length) before peak calling.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:01:05.494169+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/fragment-length-prediction-and-extension/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "MACS empirically models the shift size of ChIP-Seq tags, and uses it to improve the spatial resolution of predicted binding sites... MACS takes advantage of this bimodal pattern to empirically model the shifting size to better locate the precise binding sites... The distance between the modes of the Watson and Crick peaks in the alignment is defined as 'd', and MACS shifts all the tags by d/2 toward the 3' ends",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes empirical modeling of fragment length 'd' and tag shifting by d/2, but does NOT describe 'cross-correlation analysis' as the method. MACS uses bimodal pattern alignment of Watson/Crick strands, not cross-correlation. The card's terminology ('cross-correlation analysis') does not match the paper's actual method ('bimodal pattern alignment'). Fragment extension is mentioned implicitly (shifting tags by d/2 and extending d bases from center) but not as a separate 'pileup' step generating BEDGRAPH coverage tracks.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "fragment-length-prediction-and-extension",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Estimate the DNA fragment length (d) from ChIP-Seq data using cross-correlation analysis, then extend aligned reads to this length to generate accurate ChIP coverage tracks.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:01:17.259317+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/fragment-length-prediction-and-extension/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "MACS is implemented in Python and freely available with an open source Artistic License... It runs from the command line and takes the following parameters: -t for treatment file (ChIP tags, this is the ONLY required parameter for MACS)... --bw for bandwidth, which is half of the estimated sonication size (default 300); --pvalue for p-value cutoff to call peaks (default 1e-5); --mfold for high-confidence fold-enrichment to find model peaks for MACS modelling (default 32)",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes MACS (2008), not 'macs3'. The paper does not mention a separate 'predictd' subcommand. MACS performs fragment length modeling as part of its main peak-calling workflow, not as a standalone tool. The card references 'macs3 predictd' which appears to be a later version/refactoring not present in this 2008 paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "fragment-length-prediction-and-extension",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "macs3 predictd",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:01:17.259317+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/fragment-length-prediction-and-extension/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "Paper does not mention a 'pileup' subcommand or tool. MACS generates peak calls in BED and XLS formats with coordinates, summit, p-value, fold_enrichment, and FDR. No BEDGRAPH coverage track generation is described. The card's 'macs3 pileup' appears to be a feature of a later MACS version not documented in this 2008 paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "fragment-length-prediction-and-extension",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "macs3 pileup",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:01:17.259317+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/fragment-length-prediction-and-extension/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "MACS removes duplicate tags in excess of what is warranted by the sequencing depth (binomial distribution p-value <10-5)... After MACS shifts every tag by d/2, it slides 2d windows across the genome to find candidate peaks",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms duplicate removal and tag shifting by d/2, but does not describe a separate 'pileup coverage track' generation step. MACS outputs peak coordinates and statistics, not continuous coverage BEDGRAPH files. The scope description assumes a workflow structure (predictd \u2192 pileup) not present in the 2008 MACS paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "fragment-length-prediction-and-extension",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "After filtering duplicate reads from ChIP-Seq data but before generating pileup coverage tracks",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:01:17.259317+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
