    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/local-background-bias-estimation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "\u03bb local = max( \u03bb BG , [ \u03bb 1k ,] \u03bb 5k , \u03bb 10k ) where \u03bb 1k , \u03bb 5k and \u03bb 10k are \u03bb estimated from the 1 kb, 5 kb or 10 kb window centered at the peak location in the control sample",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes \u03bb_local as a dynamic parameter combining 1kb, 5kb, and 10kb windows via maximum operation, but uses 5kb window, not 1kb as primary short-local scale. The paper does not explicitly describe the normalization process as 'normalizing each scale relative to fragment-length baseline' \u2014 it defines \u03bb_local as max(\u03bb_BG, [\u03bb_1k,] \u03bb_5k, \u03bb_10k) where these are estimated from control or ChIP sample. The card's framing of 'pileup' generation and explicit normalization steps is not verbatim in the paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "local-background-bias-estimation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Construct a multi-scale local background noise track from control ChIP-Seq data by computing fragment-length (d), short-local (slocal, 1kb), and long-local (llocal, 10kb) pileups, normalizing each scale relative to fragment-length baseline, and combining them via maximum operatio",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:01:36.947206+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/local-background-bias-estimation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "For experiments with a control, MACS linearly scales the total control tag count to be the same as the total ChIP tag count... After MACS shifts every tag by d/2, it slides 2d windows across the genome to find candidate peaks with a significant tag enrichment (Poisson distribution p-value based on \u03bb BG , default 10-5).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly states control is scaled to match ChIP tag count, and \u03bb_local is used as the null hypothesis (Poisson distribution parameter) for peak enrichment testing.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "local-background-bias-estimation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This track is then scaled to match ChIP sequencing depth and used as the null hypothesis for peak enrichment testing.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:01:36.947206+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/local-background-bias-estimation/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "Paper does not mention 'macs3 pileup' tool or '-B flag'. The paper describes MACS (version 1, 2008), not MACS3. The paper does not describe a separate pileup generation step with explicit BEDGRAPH output. The \u03bb_local calculation is described as an internal algorithmic step, not as a separate tool invocation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "local-background-bias-estimation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "macs3 pileup \u2014 Generate fragment-length-extended pileup BEDGRAPH tracks from control reads; invoked separately for d, slocal, and llocal windows using -B flag",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:01:36.947206+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/local-background-bias-estimation/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "Paper does not mention 'macs3 bdgopt' tool or any explicit normalization via division of tracks. The \u03bb_local is computed as max(\u03bb_BG, \u03bb_1k, \u03bb_5k, \u03bb_10k) \u2014 a maximum operation on estimated parameters, not a division-based normalization of pileup tracks.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "local-background-bias-estimation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "macs3 bdgopt \u2014 Normalize slocal and llocal by dividing by d track (multiply mode with scaling factors), and add genome-wide constant to combined track",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:01:36.947206+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/local-background-bias-estimation/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "Paper does not mention 'macs3 bdgcmp' tool. The maximum operation is described as part of the \u03bb_local definition (max function), not as a separate tool step with '-m max' flag.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "local-background-bias-estimation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "macs3 bdgcmp \u2014 Compute element-wise maximum across normalized background tracks using -m max operation",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:01:36.947206+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/local-background-bias-estimation/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Sometimes the same tag can be sequenced repeatedly, more times than expected from a random genome-wide tag distribution... Therefore, MACS removes duplicate tags in excess of what is warranted by the sequencing depth (binomial distribution p-value <10-5).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes duplicate removal as part of MACS algorithm, but does not name it as a separate 'macs3 filterdup' tool. The paper describes this as an internal step applied to both ChIP and control samples, not as a prerequisite separate tool invocation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "local-background-bias-estimation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "macs3 filterdup \u2014 Remove duplicate reads from control file prior to background estimation (prerequisite step)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:01:36.947206+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/local-background-bias-estimation/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "MACS also uses a dynamic Poisson distribution to effectively capture local biases in the genome, allowing for more robust predictions... For experiments with a control, MACS linearly scales the total control tag count to be the same as the total ChIP tag count.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms that MACS uses control samples to capture local biases and improve peak calling robustness.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "local-background-bias-estimation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply this skill when you have paired ChIP and control BED/BEDPE files and need to account for local sequencing bias before peak calling.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:01:36.947206+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/local-background-bias-estimation/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "In the control samples, we often observe tag distributions with local fluctuations and biases... Many possible sources for these biases include local chromatin structure, DNA amplification and sequencing bias, and genome copy number variation. Therefore, instead of using a uniform \u03bb BG estimated from the whole genome, MACS uses a dynamic parameter, \u03bb local",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly motivates the use of dynamic local parameters over global background to handle regional biases.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "local-background-bias-estimation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Use it specifically when control signal varies across genomic regions at multiple spatial scales (e.g., open chromatin bias at 1kb and 10kb windows differs from global background), or when simple global normalization would mask true enrichment in high-background regions.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:01:36.947206+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/local-background-estimation-multiple-scales/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "\u03bb local = max( \u03bb BG , [ \u03bb 1k ,] \u03bb 5k , \u03bb 10k ) where \u03bb 1k , \u03bb 5k and \u03bb 10k are \u03bb estimated from the 1 kb, 5 kb or 10 kb window centered at the peak location in the control sample",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes \u03bb_local computed from 1 kb, 5 kb, and 10 kb windows (not 1 kb and 10 kb as card states). Card mentions 'fragment length d' as a scale, but paper uses d/2 for tag shifting, not as a separate background scale. The multi-scale approach and max operation are correct, but the specific scales differ from card description.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "local-background-estimation-multiple-scales",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
