    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/narrow-peak-coordinate-validation/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "MACS empirically models the shift size of ChIP-Seq tags, and uses it to improve the spatial resolution of predicted binding sites... The distance between the modes of the Watson and Crick peaks in the alignment is defined as 'd', and MACS shifts all the tags by d/2 toward the 3' ends to the most likely protein-DNA interaction sites. When applied to FoxA1 ChIP-Seq, which was sequenced with 3.9 million uniquely mapped tags, MACS estimates the d to be only 126 bp (Figure 1a; suggesting a tag shift size of 63 bp), despite a sonication size (bandwidth) of around 500 bp and Solexa size-selection of around 200 bp.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes MACS modeling fragment shift distance 'd' (e.g., 126 bp for FoxA1), but this is part of the main MACS algorithm, not a separate 'predictd' subcommand. The specific value ~253 bp in the card is not mentioned; the paper shows examples like 126 bp, 96 bp, 76 bp for different datasets.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "narrow-peak-coordinate-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "macs3 predictd fragment length estimate (e.g., ~253 bp)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:02:55.683338+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/poisson-statistical-enrichment-testing/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "With the current genome coverage of most ChIP-Seq experiments, tag distribution along the genome could be modeled by a Poisson distribution. The advantage of this model is that one parameter, \u03bb BG , can capture both the mean and the variance of the distribution. After MACS shifts every tag by d/2, it slides 2d windows across the genome to find candidate peaks with a significant tag enrichment (Poisson distribution p-value based on \u03bb BG , default 10-5).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper uses Poisson distribution for statistical testing; however, the card claims 'q-value scores' while the paper explicitly uses 'p-value' thresholds (default 10-5). The paper does report FDR (false discovery rate) but does not explicitly mention q-values as the primary scoring metric.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "poisson-statistical-enrichment-testing",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Applies Poisson statistics to identify genomic regions where ChIP-Seq signal significantly exceeds local background noise, computing q-value scores at single-base-pair resolution to rank peaks by statistical confidence.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:03:16.805964+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/poisson-statistical-enrichment-testing/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "After MACS shifts every tag by d/2, it slides 2d windows across the genome to find candidate peaks with a significant tag enrichment (Poisson distribution p-value based on \u03bb BG , default 10-5). Overlapping enriched peaks are merged, and each tag position is extended d bases from its center. The location with the highest fragment pileup, hereafter referred to as the summit, is predicted as the precise binding location.",
      "asbval:note": "Confirmed as intermediate step converting coverage to statistical significance; however, the paper describes this as part of 'peak detection' rather than explicitly as 'narrow peak calling'.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "poisson-statistical-enrichment-testing",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This is a critical intermediate step in narrow peak calling that converts pileup coverage and local bias estimates into statistical significance measures.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:03:16.805964+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/poisson-statistical-enrichment-testing/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "MACS is implemented in Python and freely available with an open source Artistic License at [16]. It runs from the command line and takes the following parameters: -t for treatment file (ChIP tags, this is the ONLY required parameter for MACS) and -c for control file containing mapped tags; --format for input file format in BED or ELAND (output) format (default BED); --name for name of the run (for example, FoxA1, default NA); --gsize for mappable genome size to calculate \u03bb BG from tag count (default 2.7G bp, approximately the mappable human genome size); --tsize for tag size (default 25); --bw for bandwidth, which is half of the estimated sonication size (default 300); --pvalue for p-value cutoff to call peaks (default 1e-5); --mfold for high-confidence fold-enrichment to find model peaks for MACS modelling (default 32); --diag for generating the table to evaluate sequence saturation (default off).",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes MACS (2008), not macs3. The card references 'macs3 bdgcmp' which is a later version/subcommand. The original MACS paper does not mention 'bdgcmp', 'pileup', or 'bdgopt' as separate command-line tools. These appear to be macs3-specific utilities not present in the original 2008 MACS implementation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "poisson-statistical-enrichment-testing",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "macs3 bdgcmp",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:03:16.805964+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/poisson-statistical-enrichment-testing/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "After MACS shifts every tag by d/2, it slides 2d windows across the genome to find candidate peaks with a significant tag enrichment (Poisson distribution p-value based on \u03bb BG , default 10-5). Overlapping enriched peaks are merged, and each tag position is extended d bases from its center.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes tag extension and pileup conceptually but does not name a separate 'macs3 pileup' command. The original MACS (2008) does not expose pileup as a standalone subcommand; this is a macs3 feature.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "poisson-statistical-enrichment-testing",
