    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/poisson-test-statistical-scoring/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "With the current genome coverage of most ChIP-Seq experiments, tag distribution along the genome could be modeled by a Poisson distribution. The advantage of this model is that one parameter, \u03bb BG , can capture both the mean and the variance of the distribution. After MACS shifts every tag by d/2, it slides 2d windows across the genome to find candidate peaks with a significant tag enrichment (Poisson distribution p-value based on \u03bb BG , default 10-5).",
      "asbval:note": "Poisson distribution explicitly used for p-value calculation in peak detection.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "poisson-test-statistical-scoring",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply Poisson or quasi-Poisson statistical models to compare ChIP-Seq signal against local background noise, generating p-value or q-value scores for each genomic position.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:03:38.296838+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/poisson-test-statistical-scoring/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "MACS uses \u03bb local to calculate the p-value of each candidate peak and removes potential false positives due to local biases (that is, peaks significantly under \u03bb BG , but not under \u03bb local ). Candidate peaks with p-values below a user-defined threshold p-value (default 10-5) are called, and the ratio between the ChIP-Seq tag count and \u03bb local is reported as the fold_enrichment.",
      "asbval:note": "p-values directly used for peak calling with user-defined threshold.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "poisson-test-statistical-scoring",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "transforms raw coverage comparisons into statistical significance estimates suitable for peak calling",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:03:38.296838+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/poisson-test-statistical-scoring/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "MACS is implemented in Python and freely available with an open source Artistic License at [16]. It runs from the command line and takes the following parameters: -t for treatment file (ChIP tags, this is the ONLY required parameter for MACS) and -c for control file containing mapped tags",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes MACS (original 2008 version), not macs3. The card references macs3 bdgcmp, bdgopt, bdgpeakcall, and pileup subcommands which are part of MACS3 (a later version). The original MACS paper does not mention these specific subcommands. The core functionality (Poisson comparison) is present in MACS, but the specific tool names and modular structure (bdgcmp, bdgopt, bdgpeakcall, pileup) are from MACS3, not the 2008 MACS paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "poisson-test-statistical-scoring",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "macs3 bdgcmp",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:03:38.296838+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/poisson-test-statistical-scoring/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The output includes one BED file containing the peak chromosome coordinates, and one xls file containing the genome coordinates, summit, p-value, fold_enrichment and FDR (if control is available) of each peak.",
      "asbval:note": "MACS generates coverage/pileup information implicitly during peak detection, but the 2008 paper does not describe a separate 'pileup' subcommand. This is a MACS3 feature not present in the original MACS.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "poisson-test-statistical-scoring",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "macs3 pileup",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:03:38.296838+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/poisson-test-statistical-scoring/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "No mention of a 'bdgopt' tool or subcommand in the MACS 2008 paper. MACS does scale control tags (\"MACS linearly scales the total control tag count to be the same as the total ChIP tag count\") but this is internal to the algorithm, not a separate command-line tool.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "poisson-test-statistical-scoring",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "macs3 bdgopt",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:03:38.296838+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/poisson-test-statistical-scoring/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Candidate peaks with p-values below a user-defined threshold p-value (default 10-5) are called",
      "asbval:note": "MACS does threshold peaks by p-value, but the 2008 paper does not describe a separate 'bdgpeakcall' subcommand. This is a MACS3 modularization not present in the original MACS.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "poisson-test-statistical-scoring",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "macs3 bdgpeakcall",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:03:38.296838+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/poisson-test-statistical-scoring/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "MACS uses a dynamic parameter, \u03bb local , defined for each candidate peak as: \u03bb local = max( \u03bb BG , [ \u03bb 1k ,] \u03bb 5k , \u03bb 10k ) where \u03bb 1k , \u03bb 5k and \u03bb 10k are \u03bb estimated from the 1 kb, 5 kb or 10 kb window centered at the peak location in the control sample, or the ChIP-Seq sample when a control sample is not available",
      "asbval:note": "MACS does compute local lambda at multiple scales (1kb, 5kb, 10kb), but the paper does not explicitly describe generating separate BEDGRAPH track files as intermediate outputs. The computation is internal to MACS.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "poisson-test-statistical-scoring",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "After generating ChIP pileup and local lambda (background) BEDGRAPH tracks with matched sequencing depth",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:03:38.296838+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/poisson-test-statistical-scoring/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "The scope section is incomplete/truncated in the card. The paper does mention 'd' (the shift distance) and \u03bb_local, but the scope text cuts off mid-sentence and does not provide a complete criterion.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2008-9-9-r137",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "poisson-test-statistical-scoring",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Local background was not properly constructed from d, slocal",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:03:38.296838+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
